Data Generation: Values are simulated based on Dennisâ€™s mock ranges ($ V_1, V_2 \in [0.5, 2] $, $ \rho_{12} $ per regime), with noise $ \epsilon \sim \mathcal{N}(0, 0.001) $ and $ \Omega_{\text{pred}} $ derived from $ \lambda_{\Omega} \approx 1 $ (placeholder until fitted).
Regime Assignment: Near-zero (1â€“10), anti-aligned with both orders (11â€“30) to test antisymmetry.





